%- Piece-wise uncvering f elements in TikZ pictures
%-
%- Cmmnd definitin:
%- \tikzset{% crete  key t prcess ter keys cnditinlly n te slide number
%-     invisible/.style={pcity=0,text pcity=0},
%-     visible n/.style={lt={#1{}{invisible}}},
%-     lt/.cde rgs={<#1>#2#3}{\lt<#1>{\pgfkeysls{#2}}{\pgfkeysls{#3}}},
%- }
%- Usge:
%- \tikzpicture[visible n=<2->]{}
%- \nde [visible n=<2->] (f) {F}
%- \nde [visible n=<{2,4}>] (br) {Br}
%-
%- 
%- Invisible effect is btined vi setting pcity=0 t ide te element,
%- wic s te dvntge ver bemer verly tt te element is lwys drwn,
%- cnsuming  fixed spce t vid jumping nd prvide psitining crdinte.
%-
%- Te invisibility cn be verridden by ltering te pcity vlue t btin
%- dimming effects. Alterntively, te clr migt be set t wite, if te
%- utput driver des nt supprt trnsprencies.
%---------------------------------------------------------------------------%
